        "timestamp": "2018-05-03 13:39:54.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Kiram,\nA few questions:\n\n1) why is not SMS colocated with AAF VM?\n\n2) sms_install script uses a template for ubuntu 1404, while SMS uses ubuntu 1604. If you look at other install scripts that use 1604 (like so_install.sh), you'll see that the docker repository is different (xenial vs. trusty) and the vNIC is renamed from ens* to eth* (towards the end of the script).\n\n3) dns_install.sh requires also a sed instruction in the openecomp section.\n\nThanks,\nMarco",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "f89188fdc7a327b27f2cb3b332a0a4948b347776",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 301,
          "name": "Kiran Kamineni",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "kiran.k.kamineni@intel.com",
          "username": "kirankamineni"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-05-03 17:02:10.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Hi Kiram,\n > A few questions:\n > \n > 1) why is not SMS colocated with AAF VM?\n > \n > 2) sms_install script uses a template for ubuntu 1404, while SMS\n > uses ubuntu 1604. If you look at other install scripts that use\n > 1604 (like so_install.sh), you'll see that the docker repository is\n > different (xenial vs. trusty) and the vNIC is renamed from ens* to\n > eth* (towards the end of the script).\n > \n > 3) dns_install.sh requires also a sed instruction in the openecomp\n > section.\n > \n > Thanks,\n > Marco\n\nI didn't colocate it with AAF as I was not sure how to do that and I also didn't want to create any dependencies between the two during startup. \n\nI will fix the other things your mentioned.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
